<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1562,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1562,1588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Eyes separated by 
<number box="[568,583,1562,1588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
facet diameters; wing membrane with small bristles in the costal and cubital areas; gonostylus with small basal lobe with long bristles; cercus piriform with cluster of accessory tenacula confined to a dark area near the base; aedeagal apodeme oval-shaped, same length as paramere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1562,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1682,1708]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Head (
<figureCitation box="[512,581,1682,1708]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[567,581,1682,1708]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
): vertex hair patch divided by a narrow medial band without bristles, Vshaped; eyes separated by 
<number box="[472,487,1722,1748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
facet diameters; interocular suture arched; frons hair patch undivided, anterior margin with small median concavity. Antenna: scape cylindrical, 1.8X length of pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1324,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1307,1324,1762,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); pedicel spherical (
<figureCitation box="[280,359,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[342,359,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); flagellum with 
<number box="[582,611,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="14.0">14</number>
flagellomeres, fusiform; all flagellomeres with neck (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1419,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Figs. 
<number box="[1367,1419,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.3">2, 3</number>
</figureCitation>
); flagellomere 
<number box="[306,335,1842,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="14.0">14</number>
smaller than preceding ones and with apiculus (
<figureCitation box="[897,968,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[952,968,1842,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); ascoids not visible; one 
<typeStatus box="[1271,1372,1842,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">paratype</typeStatus>
male with flagellomeres 
<number box="[380,395,1882,1908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[456,471,1882,1908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
fused (
<figureCitation box="[561,635,1882,1908]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[617,635,1882,1908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Palpus formula = 1.0:2.0:1.9:2.9; last palpomere striated (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1421,1882,1908]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1404,1421,1882,1908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing: wing membrane with infuscate patterns: a large dark area near the middle of the wing, with smaller darker spots in the costal region, base of M 
<number box="[666,672,1979,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[682,691,1979,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
, apex of the wing tip, and apex of M 
<number box="[1135,1143,1979,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
and M 
<number box="[1229,1237,1979,1993]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1254,1327,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1310,1327,1962,1988]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); bristles present in costal and cubital areas (
<figureCitation box="[564,636,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[619,636,2005,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); Sc short; radial fork basal to medial fork; R 
<number box="[1173,1181,2021,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" value="5.0">5</number>
ending at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1377,1436,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[170,1412,672,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,661,1872]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male. Figs. 1 – 7, holotype, except of 1 and 4 (paratype). 1. Head. 2. Antenna: scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres. 3. Antenna: flagellomeres 12 – 14. 4. Antenna: right flagelomeres 1 – 2 fused. 5. Palpus. 6. Wing with the infuscate pattern. 7. Wing with the distribution of bristles in the wing membrane." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182662/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">Figs.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
<number box="[151,197,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="6.7">6, 7</number>
). Male terminalia: hypandrium reduced, only a post-hypandrial plate present with length equal to 0.4X the length of aedeagal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[500,573,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[556,573,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); apex of post-hypandrial plate sickle-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1201,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[1184,1201,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite short, 
<number box="[151,161,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<date box="[171,210,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
<number box="[171,185,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
the length of gonostylus, with few very short bristles on the dorsal surface and few long bristles on the ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[341,455,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 
<number box="[408,455,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxal apodeme 
<number box="[728,738,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<date box="[748,787,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
<number box="[748,762,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
the length of aedeagal apodeme, with sclerotized anterior band (
<figureCitation box="[276,349,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,349,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonostylus slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[708,780,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[764,780,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), digitiform, except by the presence of a basal tubercle with long bristles (
<figureCitation box="[379,498,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 
<number box="[449,498,352,378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
); alveoli present along entire surface (
<figureCitation box="[965,1040,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[1023,1040,352,378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium subquadrate, naked (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,246,392,418]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); foramen not visible. Cerci piriform, narrow apically, wide basally with one apical tenaculum, short, filiform (
<figureCitation box="[260,333,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[317,333,432,458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), with two small bristles near the tenaculum; cluster of accessory tenacula confined to dark area near the base, with clavate tips (
<figureCitation box="[580,652,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[635,652,472,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sternite 
<number box="[771,800,472,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
short, ending before distal margin of epandrium; apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[266,356,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,356,512,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergite 
<number box="[471,500,512,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
narrow (
<figureCitation box="[612,703,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[670,703,512,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus wider than paramere, with rounded apex, ending before paramere (
<figureCitation box="[360,475,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 
<number box="[427,475,552,578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus 0.8X the length of paramere. Paramere subtriangular, narrow apically (
<figureCitation box="[159,233,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,233,592,618]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme oval-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[651,780,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 
<number box="[719,780,592,618]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="9.11">9, 11</number>
</figureCitation>
), same length as paramere, with length 2.0X the width (
<figureCitation box="[159,272,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1418,1442]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,193,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,172,1426]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. 8 – 11. Alepia montana Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia. Figs. 8 – 11 holotype, except of 8 (paratype). 8. Lateral. 9. Dorsal. 10. Ventral. 11. Aedeagal apodeme. 12. Alepia arenivaga Bravo, sp. nov., male terminalia, aedeagal apodeme, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182663/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 
<number box="[226,272,632,658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="55" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
